title: Millwall's shock FA Cup win over Leicester marred as home fans invade pitch and 'launch missiles at Foxes supporters'
text:
Sport Millwall's shock FA Cup win over Leicester marred as home fans invade pitch and 'launch missiles at Foxes supporters' Police horses were employed after the final whistle as some Lions' fans goaded Leicester supporters following the slender win Share Police horses enter the pitch to quell Millwall fans who had taunted Leicester fans (Photo: Plumb Images) Share   Thank you for subscribing!   
Millwall poured more misery on Premier League champions Leicester City, sending them out of the FA Cup. 
Shaun Cummings' late goal was enough to earn the 10-man Lions a place in the quarter-finals but the win was marred by some ugly scenes at the end of the game. 
Millwall supporters stormed the pitch in celebration of their shock win over Claudio Ranieri's side, but some chose to head towards the away end to taunt the Foxes supporters. 
And after a short while some missiles were launched into the away end, prompting police officers on horses to enter the pitch to move the fans on. 
Some Leicester fans reported Millwall fans goading them and launching missiles into the away end.. 
After already dumping out Bournemouth and Watford, Neil Harris' Lions shrugged off the dismissal of defender Jake Cooper to grab a last-minute winner from right-back Shaun Cummings and heap more misery on Claudio Ranieri and Premier League champions Leicester . 
Cooper was sent off after being shown two yellow cards either side of the break and Millwall were indebted to keeper Jordan Archer for keeping them in the tie. Shaun Cummings had won it for Millwall (Photo: Clive Rose) Millwall fans entered the pitch after the game (Photo: Plumb Images) Some Millwall fans taunted Leicester supporters (Photo: Plumb Images) Police horses were deployed to break up some fans (Photo: Ian Walton) Fans goaded Leicester supporters after the win (Photo: Plumb Images) It marred a shock win for Millwall in the FA Cup (Photo: Ian Walton) 
Archer reacted quickly to turn away Shinji Okazaki's first half header before producing a brilliant block to deny the Leicester striker when he seemed certain to score, minutes from the end. 
And Archer's heroics paved the way for Cummings to win the match at the death after he raced onto Lee Gregory's chest down and kept his cool to score. 
But the win has been marred by some fans' behaviour after the final whistle. poll loading Will Millwall face punishment for their fans' behaviour? 0+ VOTES SO FAR
